% ---------------- primary comparison: Black 2017 ------------------------

\subsection{Primary benchmark: Black et~al.\ 2017}

Black et~al.~\citep{black2017openephyseeg} adapt commercial EEG caps onto the
Open Ephys acquisition board via a custom breakout-to-Omnetics-to-Intan-
headstage chain. The abstract reports: \emph{``The Open Ephys + EEG system
can record reliable human EEG data, as well as human EMG data. A
side-by-side comparison of eyes closed 8--14 Hz activity between the Open
Ephys + EEG system and the Brainvision ActiCHamp EEG system showed similar
average power and signal to noise.''} Three consequences for \freeeeg{}
design follow directly:

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
\item \textbf{Validation protocol}. Eyes-closed 8--14\,Hz alpha power and
SNR, side-by-side against a BrainVision actiCHamp clinical amplifier, is
the \emph{minimum} bar to call anything ``beta.'' We adopt it verbatim as
the \freeeeg{}-beta acceptance gate (Section~\ref{sec:validation}).
\item \textbf{Commercial-cap adapter pathway}. Their breakout-PCB model is a
template for a sister \freeeeg{}-amp variant that accepts any commercial
EasyCap-class cap. Worth prototyping after the beta lands.
\item \textbf{Plugin-GUI integration}. Their stack is native to the Open
Ephys GUI. We plan an equivalent acquisition plugin for \freeeeg{}, and
the corresponding native plugin for MNE Scan (Section~\ref{sec:apps}).
\end{itemize}

Table~\ref{tab:vs-black} gives the feature-level comparison.

