% ===========================================================================
\section{System architecture}
% ===========================================================================

\subsection{Alpha board overview}

Figure~\ref{fig:alpha-arch} diagrams the alpha acquisition chain. One hundred
thirty passive dry Ag/AgCl electrodes on a 10/5-system textile cap
(DC resistance $\leq$ 500~$\Omega$, 12~mm diameter, multi-prong) terminate
in 1.5~mm DIN touch-proof plugs that mate into a custom passive brain-box.
The brain-box fans the 128 channels (128 signal + CP1 reference + CP2
ground) into sixteen Texas Instruments ADS131M08 $\Delta\Sigma$
ADCs~\citep{ti_ads131m08}, eight channels per chip, arranged with a
deliberately scrambled mapping that assigns topographically distant
electrodes to the same ADC package in order to maximize across-ADC
signal independence. The ADCs run at gain 32, reference voltage 1.25~V,
and an on-board firmware-configured sample rate of 250~Hz.

